text:
Well, recall the formula

H = (1 - 1/R_0) / E

H = herd immunity proportion from vaccination,
R_0 = Basic reproduction number
E = vaccine efficacy.

For 50.4% efficacy to work with H < 100%, then 

(1 - 1/R_0) / E < 1
--> 1 - 1/R_0 < E 
--> 1 - E < 1/R_0
--> R_0 < 1/(1 - E)
name: Peter Cayton, the Stats Guy
